### Description
- Type: Bug
- Priority: Major 

The write of a FOTA image to internal flash results in incorrect data being written to internal flash on Odin platforms.  This results in a failed hash compare using the application
https://github.com/ARMmbed/fota-demo/commit/aefc7b93fa904d98fd438873c7293b565e5c2eff

Some debug has been done on the issue (details below).
Down-revving the flash driver per 
https://github.com/ARMmbed/mbed-bootloader-internal/pull/41
seems to eliminate the issue.

---------------------------------------------------------------
## Bug

**Target**
UBLOX_EVK_ODIN_W2

**Toolchain:**
GCC_ARM

**mbed-cli version:** 
1.2.2

**mbed-os sha:**
6e0d01cd1 (tag: mbed_lib_rev153, tag: mbed-os-5.6.2, tag: latest) Merge pull request #5268 from ARMmbed/release-candidate

**Expected behavior**
Data read from flash matches the source dat used to program (write to) flash.

**Actual behavior**
flash.program() returns a success return code but on a subsequent read, the data (at the same address) does not match the data provided on the write.

Possible relevant details from debug:

- data in this instance was being written in 1024 byte chunks.  A large majority of writes were successful
- The first unsuccessful write occurred at flash address 0x08100000 which corresponds to the start of the second bank of flash.  This is followed by both successful and unsuccessful writes.
- The failure is consistent with the same incorrect data being written to the same addresses on each successive run.  (The SHA of the incorrect image is consistent from run to run)
- The following code snippet and log output illustrates the issue (note this code was added for debug and is not present in the commit referenced above.)

```
